        public static string[] Elephants = { "An elephant is the world’s largest land animal.", "An elephant’s tusk weight may exceed up to 200 kg.", "The largest elephant was an African elephant, weighed around 24,000 pounds and was 13 feet tall.", "The largest elephant was an African elephant, weighed around 24,000 pounds and was 13 feet tall.", "An elephant is the only mammal who can’t jump.", "Elephant’s average lifespan is around 60 to 70 years old.", "Elephant’s trunk has more than 40,000 muscles.", "August 12th is World’s Elephant Day.", "Male elephants are called bulls and females are called cows.", "Elephants don’t like peanuts.", "An elephant needs around 300 kg of food & 160 liters of water each day.", "An elephant’s heart average weight is around 27 to 46 pounds.", "An Asian elephant can hold 8.5 L of water in its trunk.", "An Asian elephant can hold 8.5 L of water in its trunk", "The brain of an elephant is 3 or 4 times larger than humans.", "Elephants have an amazing sense of smell.", "Elephants generally sleep 2 to 3 hours each day.", "An elephant can reproduce at the age of sixteen.", "In 1903, Edison electrocuted an elephant to demonstrate that Tesla’s AC current was fatal.", "A baby elephant is called a calf.", "A baby elephant is called a calf - Serious Facts", "Elephants can understand human-like emotions such as feeling a loss, grieving and even crying.", "Elephants have the longest gestation period of all the animals, 22 months.", "Elephants use their incisor teeth for defense, digging for water and lifting things.", "Elephants have four molars. One molar can weigh around five pounds.", "Like humans, Elephants have death rituals.", "Elephants waive their trunks to smell better.", "Elephants can identify themselves in a mirror.", "The Kenya Wildlife Service has documented the killing of 97 elephants so far this year.", "Elephants use sand or mud to keep themselves safe from sunburned.", "Newborn elephants are born blind & stand up shortly after 